The paper deals with a problem of assigning transmission ranges to radio stations in a communication network, which involves concepts from graph theory, optimization, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which covers topics related to algorithm design and analysis. The problem also has applications in network engineering (cs.NE), computational geometry (cs.CG), information theory (cs.IT), and signal processing (cs.SI).
